edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.image
Class ImageSet

java.lang.Object
  edu.stanford.cfuller.imageanalysistools.image.ImageSet
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.io.Serializable, java.lang.Iterable<Image>, java.util.Collection<Image>
public class ImageSet
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.io.Serializable, java.util.Collection<Image>

A set of related Images that will be processed together for analysis. For instance, multiple channels of the same Image might be collected into an ImageSet. Images in the set can be added by Image object, by filename, or by omero Id. Optionally, one Image in the set can be designated as a marker Image, which might have some specific purpose in the analysis. For instance, the marker Image might be the Image to use for segmentation, while the others might just be quantified. Images added by filename or omero Id must be loaded using loadAllImages() before being used or retrieved.

Author:
Colin J. Fuller

setMarkerImage

public void setMarkerImage(int index)
Specifies that the Image at the provided index is the marker Image. The index refers to the order in which the Image was added to the ImageSet. (Starts at 0.) Supply -1 for the index as a shortcut for the most recently added Image.

Parameters:
index - The index of the Image to designate as the marker Image.

disposeImages

public void disposeImages()
Disposes of the memory-intensive portions of Images. Useful for programs that retain long-term references to the ImageSet for things like naming, but don't need the pixel data for the full lifetime of the ImageSet.
